equipment.name: EZ-Curl Bar
equipment.description: Angled grip barbell for curls and tricep work

exercises.name: Squat
exercises.form_notes: Brace core, break at hips and knees together, drive through whole foot

exercises.name: Bench Press
exercises.form_notes: Retract shoulder blades, arch upper back, drive feet into floor

exercises.name: Deadlift
exercises.form_notes: Brace core, push the floor away, lock hips and knees together

exercises.name: Overhead Press
exercises.form_notes: Squeeze glutes, brace core, press straight up, move head through at lockout

exercises.name: Barbell Row
exercises.form_notes: Hinge at hips, pull to lower chest, squeeze shoulder blades together

programs.name: 5/3/1 for Beginners
programs.description: Wendler's 5/3/1 adapted for beginners (thefitness.wiki). Two main lifts per day with First Set Last (FSL) 5x5 supplemental. 3-week cycles. Accessories: 50-100 reps each of push, pull, and single-leg/core after main work.

programs.name: 5/3/1 BBB
programs.description: Wendler's 5/3/1 Boring But Big. One main lift per day with 5x10 supplemental at 50% TM for hypertrophy. 3-week cycles. Accessories: 25-50 reps each of push, pull, and single-leg/core after main + BBB work.

programs.name: Phrak's Greyskull LP
programs.description: Phrak's variant of Greyskull LP (r/Fitness recommended). Alternating A/B workouts, 3 days per week. All lifts use 3x5+ (AMRAP last set) except Deadlift which is 1x5+. Progression is per session. Deload 10% on failure.

programs.name: GZCLP
programs.description: Cody Lefever's GZCLP linear progression. Three tiers per day: T1 heavy 5x3+ (AMRAP last set), T2 volume 3x10, T3 pump 3x15+ (AMRAP last set). Progression is per session. Failure protocols: T1 5x3 -> 6x2 -> 10x1 -> reset; T2 3x10 -> 3x8 -> 3x6 -> add weight restart; T3 add weight when AMRAP hits 25 reps.
